To display a date in MySQL, you can simply use the SELECT statement to get the date:
```sql
SELECT MySQL_Date_Col FROM table_name;
```
If you want to display the MySQL date in a specific format, such as mm-dd-yyyy, you can use the MySQL DATE_FORMAT function:
```sql
SELECT DATE_FORMAT(MySQL_Date_Col, '%m-%d-%Y')
FROM table_name;
```
This will retrieve the date from the MySQL_Date_Col column in the table_name, and format it as mm-dd-yyyy.

To display a count of MySQL rows for each day of the month, you can use the DAYOFMONTH function along with the COUNT function:
```sql
SELECT COUNT(id), DAYOFMONTH(MySQL_Date_Col)
FROM table_name
GROUP BY DAYOFMONTH(MySQL_Date_Col);
```
This will retrieve count of MySQL rows for each day of the month, taking into account MySQL_Date_Col column and groups them by DAYOFMONTH function.
